{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"18321","heading":"Human space flight beyond low-Earth orbit","label":"18321 Human space flight beyond low-Earth orbit","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch159/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Findings","label":"a Findings","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The extension of the human presence from low-Earth orbit to other regions of space beyond low-Earth orbit will enable missions to the surface of the Moon and missions to deep space destinations such as near-Earth asteroids and Mars.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The regions of cis-lunar space are accessible to other national and commercial launch capabilities, and such access raises a host of national security concerns and economic implications that international human space endeavors can help to address.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The ability to support human missions in regions beyond low-Earth orbit and on the surface of the Moon can also drive developments in emerging areas of space infrastructure and technology.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Developments in space infrastructure and technology can stimulate and enable increased space applications, such as in-space servicing, propellant resupply and transfer, and in situ resource utilization, and open opportunities for additional users of space, whether national, commercial, or international.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A long term objective for human exploration of space should be the eventual international exploration of Mars.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Future international missions beyond low-Earth orbit should be designed to incorporate capability development and availability, affordability, and international contributions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fa%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Human space flight and future exploration beyond low-Earth orbit should be based around a pay-as-you-go approach. Requirements in new launch and crew systems authorized in this chapter should be scaled to the minimum necessary to meet the core national mission capability needed to conduct cis-lunar missions. These initial missions, along with the development of new technologies and in-space capabilities can form the foundation for missions to other destinations. These initial missions also should provide operational experience prior to the further human expansion into space.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Report on international collaboration","label":"b Report on international collaboration","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Report required","label":"1 Report required","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any effort by NASA to expand and ensure effective international collaboration on the ISS.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The efforts of NASA, including its approach and progress, in defining near-term, cis-lunar space human missions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"NASA contributions","label":"2 NASA contributions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A Space Launch System.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A multi-purpose crew vehicle.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18321/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18321%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Such other technology elements the Administrator may consider appropriate, and which the Administrator shall specifically identify in the report.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
